{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17614308","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17614308"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:43:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:43:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16359"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16359","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16359"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.12,0.15,0.62,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9050"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116489"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9050","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9050"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16359"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98482"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4904"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7184"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21521"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21526"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116489","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116489"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe brainstem contains various cranial nerve nuclei arranged in specific locations from the midbrain to the medulla oblongata.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following cranial nerves has its nuclei located in the upper cervical spinal cord and medulla?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oculomotor nerve","Hypoglossal nerve","Abducens nerve","Spinal accessory nerve","Glossopharyngeal nerve"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Espinal accessory nerve\u003C/strong\u003E is unique among cranial nerves as it has nuclei located in both the upper cervical spinal cord (C1-C5) and the medulla oblongata. The spinal component innervates the sternocleidomastoid and trapezius muscles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eoculomotor nerve\u003C/strong\u003E nuclei (motor and parasympathetic) are located in the midbrain. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypoglossal nerve\u003C/strong\u003E nucleus is located in the medulla. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eabducens nerve\u003C/strong\u003E nucleus is located in the pons. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eglossopharyngeal nerve\u003C/strong\u003E nuclei are located in the medulla.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the location of cranial nerve nuclei is important for localising lesions in the brainstem.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The spinal accessory nerve (cranial nerve XI) has its motor nuclei located in both the upper cervical spinal cord (C1-C5) and medulla oblongata.","The spinal component innervates the sternocleidomastoid and trapezius muscles, while the cranial component joins the vagus nerve."],"references":["Roberts, S.O., Cardozo, A. A detailed review of the spinal accessory nerve and its anatomical variations with cadaveric illustration. Anat Sci Int 99, 239\u2013253 (2024). https://doi.org/10.1007/s12565-024-00770-w","Netter, F. H. (2015). Netter\u0027s Cranial Nerve Collection E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98482"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16359"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[